  "texts": [
    "Many concept learning methods use it, including CaCE [141], DISSECT [162], GlanceNets [171], and [172].",
    "Fig. 10 Samples of BRODEN dataset.",
    "Each pair images from left to right: concept 'Object' (flower), concept 'Color' (pink), concept 'Object Part' (headboard), concept 'Scene' (street), and concept 'Texture' (swirly) Fig. 11 CelebA dataset concept samples.",
    "Each pair images from left to right: concept 'Eyeglasses', concept 'Bangs', concept 'Wavy Hair', concept 'Mustache', concept 'Smiling' dSprites datasetThe work in [127] proposed well-created 2D shape samples, which are frequently used in unsupervised approaches.",
    "It consists of six concept labels with their defined values: 'Color' [White], 'Shape' [square, ellipse, heart], 'Scale' [6 values linearly spaced in [0.5, 1]], 'Orientation' [40 values in [0, 2 pi]], 'Position X' [32 values in [0, 1]], 'Position Y' [32 values in [0, 1]], which generate over 737 K image samples."
